Justin Randall Timberlake (born January 31, 1981) is an American singer-songwriter, actor and entrepreneur. He became extremely popular while being a part of N'Sync boys' band by the end of nineties and beginning of the 21 century. In 2002 he had decided to record his own solo album "Justified" which became multi -platinum a few weeks after the release. The album become so popular mostly to the hit "Cry me a river". Justin was born in the last day of January 1981 in Memphis, as the legend says, as soon as he started walking and talking the boy already was showing signs of a great singing and dancing talent. When he was eleven he appeared in TV in a competition "Star search". That was the time when he under the pen name Justin Randall performed a few songs in a country style. As a result he was noticed by producers and invited to the popular Disney TV show The New Mickey Mouse Club, where he worked with such young talent.
